devdoc.details: Uses Auth contract for 2-step owner process and trust operators to guard functions

acceptOwnership().details: The new owner accepts the ownership transfer.

doAction(address,uint256,bytes).details: can only be called by owner

params._value: The amount of eth to send with the call
params.data: The data to be sent with the call
params.to: The address to send the call to

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

pendingOwner().details: Returns the address of the pending owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

snwap(address,uint256,address,address,ui.details: Must be called by a trusted operator

params.amountIn: Amount of the input token to swap
params.amountOutMin: Minimum acceptable amount of output tokens (slippage protection)
params.executor: Address of the executor contract to perform the swap logic
params.executorData: Encoded data for the executor call
params.recipient: Address to receive the output tokens

returns.amountOut: The actual amount of output tokens received

snwapMultiple((address,uint256,address)[.details: Must be called by a trusted operator

params.executors: Array of executor calls to perform

returns.amountOut: Array of actual amounts of output tokens received

transferOwnership(address).details: Starts the ownership transfer of the contract to a new account. Replaces the pending transfer if there is one. Can only be called by the current owner.

updateRedSnwapper(address).details: make sure new RedSnwapper is backwards compatiable (should be)

params._redSnwapper: The address of the new route processor

withdraw(address,address,uint256).details: can only be called by owner

params._value: The amount of the token to be withdrawn
params.to: The address to send the token to
params.token: The address of the token to be withdrawn, 0x0 for eth
